HEADWORD: embarrassing
<hw>embarrassing</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>hard to deal
with; <as>as, greeted with an <ex>embarrassing</ex>
silence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> awkward, disconcerting, off-putting, sticky, tight,
unenviable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>causing to feel shame or chagrin or
vexation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mortifying, shame-making.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

